Skeleton.
Ectosomal region with (para)tangential bundles of styles or, alternatively, fanning out in bouquets or brushes obliquely to the surface. In addition, several debris (sandy grains) can be seen (
Fig. 6 D
). Choanosomal region with several wide and rounded canals throughout the skeleton, up to ca. 1000 wide, and multispicular tracts of styles in a slightly irregular mesh (
Fig. 6E
).

